headline.main: WHY WHEELER DOESN'T FEAR HITLER; WHY WHEELER DOESN'T FEAR HITLER

lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON. IF by some fortuitous circumstance it fell to the lot of Senator Wheeler of Montana to reorganize the world, he says he would cut the United States completely loose from the rest of it and make of this country a "strong, silent, self-contained, successful democracy."
